#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[ala]]Atlas of Living Australia (ALA)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:6
msgid "The ALA is a web-based platform that pulls together Australian biodiversity data from multiple sources, making it accessible and reusable to anyone (see https://www.ala.org.au/about-ala/). The open infrastructure platform developed by the ALA is also used by several other countries for their own national biodiversity data platform (see https://living-atlases.gbif.org/)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[asv]]Amplicon Sequence Variant (ASV)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:7
msgid "Unique DNA sequence derived from high-throughput sequencing and denoising, and assumed to represent a biologically real sequence variant. See also <<otu,Operational Taxonomic Unit (OTU)>> and https://doi.org/10.1038/ismej.2017.119[(Callahan et al. 2017)^]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[api]]Application Programming Interface (API)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:8
msgid "Set of protocols and tools for interaction and data transmission between different computer applications."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[bins]]Barcode Index Numbers (BINs)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:9
msgid "Species-level <<otu,Operational Taxonomic Units (OTUs)>> derived from clustering of the cytochrome c oxidase I (COI) gene in animals. Each BIN is assigned a globally unique identifier, and is made available in searchable database within the <<bold,Barcode of Life Data System (BOLD)>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[bold]]Barcode of Life Data System (BOLD)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:10
msgid "http://www.boldsystems.org/[BOLD^] is the reference database maintained by the Centre for Biodiversity Genomics in Guelph on behalf of the International Barcode of Life Consortium (https://ibol.org/[IBOL^]). It hosts data on barcode reference specimens and sequences for eukaryote species, particularly COI for animals, and maintains the Barcode Index Number (http://www.boldsystems.org/index.php/Public_BarcodeIndexNumber_Home[BIN^]; https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0066213[Ratnasingham & Hebert 2013^]) system, identifiers for OTUs of approximately species rank, based on clusters of closely similar sequences."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[biodiversity-data-platform]]Biodiversity data platform"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:11
msgid "General online resource to discover and access biodiversity data derived from various sources, such as natural history collections, citizen science, ecology and monitoring projects, and genetic sequences. Can be global (<<gbif,GBIF>>) or national (<<ala,ALA>>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[clustering]]Clustering"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:12
msgid "In taxonomic classification, the process of grouping organisms together according to some similarity criterion. See <<otu,Operational Taxonomic Unit>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[community-dna]]Community (bulk) DNA"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:13
msgid "DNA from bulk samples (e.g. plankton samples or Malaise trap samples consisting of several individuals from many species). For the purpose of this guide, bulk sample DNA is included in the eDNA concept."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[dwc-a]]Darwin Core Archive (DwC-A)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:14
msgid "Compressed (ZIP) file format for exchange of biodiversity data compiled in accordance with the <<dwc-standard,Darwin Core (DwC) standard>>. Essentially a self-contained set of interconnected CSV files and an XML document describing included files and data columns, and their mutual relationships."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[dwc-standard]]Darwin Core (DwC) standard"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:15
msgid "Standard for sharing and publishing biodiversity data, originating from the Biodiversity Information Standards (TDWG) community. In principle, a set of terms used for describing different entities of biodiversity observations, such as sampling events, occurrences and taxa. Current Darwin Core terms are described in the https://dwc.tdwg.org/terms/[Quick Reference Guide]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[data-vocabulary]]Data vocabulary"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:17
msgid "Set of preferred terms or concepts with specific, well-defined meanings and interrelationships, facilitating data exchange and reuse."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[ddpcr]]ddPCR (droplet digital Polymerase Chain Reaction)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:18
msgid "Droplet digital <<pcr,PCR>>. Method for measuring absolute amount of DNA (number of copies) of one marker in a sample. See also <<qpcr,qPCR>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[denoising]]Denoising"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:19
msgid "In metabarcoding, method for separation of true biological sequences (see <<asv,ASVs>>) from spurious sequence variants caused by PCR amplification and sequencing error."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[doi]]Digital Object Identifier (DOI)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:20
msgid "Long-lasting reference used to uniquely identify (and locate) digital information objects, such as a biodiversity data set or a scientific publication."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[barcoding]]DNA barcoding and metabarcoding (amplicon sequencing)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:21
msgid "Use of short, standardized DNA fragments to identify individual organisms via sequencing. Metabarcoding combines barcoding with high-throughput DNA sequencing, using universal primers to amplify and sequence large groups of organisms in eDNA samples."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[dna-marker]]DNA marker"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:22
msgid "A DNA fragment used as a marker of some property (e.g., taxonomic affiliation). May, but does not have to, be a gene or a part of a gene."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[dna-db]]DNA metabarcoding database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:23
msgid "Database containing DNA sequences (DNA barcodes) from previously recovered or studied organisms. The reference sequences were ideally generated from individuals of described, well-studied species-with the type specimen serving as the ideal-or higher taxonomic level (e.g., genus, family), but may also stem from eDNA sequencing efforts. It is wise not to trust “reference sequences” blindly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[dna-probe]]DNA probe"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:24
msgid "A short, synthetic single-stranded DNA fragment with fluorescent labelling that binds to a selected region of target DNA (marker) during PCR. Increases specificity and can be used in addition to primers in <<qpcr,qPCR>> and <<ddpcr,ddPCR>> to detect and quantify a genetic marker."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[embl]]European Bioinformatics Institute (EMBL-EBI)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:25
msgid "Intergovernmental organization for bioinformatics research and services, part of the European Molecular Biology Laboratory (EMBL), providing eg. (raw) sequence reads and assembly data via <<ena,the European Nucleotide Archive (ENA)>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[edna]]Environmental DNA (eDNA)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:26
msgid "DNA from an environmental sample, e.g. soil, water, air or host organism. An often used definition is that environmental DNA is the genetic material (DNA) obtained from environmental samples without any obvious evidence of biological source material (https://doi.org/10.1016/j.biocon.2014.11.019[Thomsen and Willerslev 2015^])."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[ena]]European Nucleotide Archive (ENA)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:27
msgid "European repository for nucleotide sequences, covering raw sequencing data, sequence assembly information and functional annotation. Includes the <<sra,Sequence Read Archive (SRA)>>, and is maintained by the European Bioinformatics Institute (EMBL-EBI), as part of <<insdc, the International Nucleotide Sequence Database Collaboration (INSDC)>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[fastq]]FASTQ"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:28
msgid "Text-based standard for storing molecular sequences and associated quality measures deriving from <<hts,High-throughput sequencing (HTS)>>. For each sequence position, single ASCII-characters are used to represent base call (identified nucleotide) and score, respectively."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[gbif]]Global Biodiversity Information Facility (GBIF)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:29
msgid "International network and research infrastructure, mainly focused on mobilizing and providing open access to global biodiversity data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[ggbn]]Global Genome Biodiversity Network (GGBN)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:30
msgid "International network of institutions concerned with efficient sharing and usage of genomic biodiversity samples and associated metadata, e.g. promoting the Darwin Core-compatible GGBN Data Standard."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[gps]]Global Positioning System (GPS)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:31
msgid "Satellite navigation system operated by the United States Space Force."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[hts]]High-throughput sequencing (HTS)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:32
msgid "Different technologies for massively parallel sequencing, producing millions of DNA sequence reads from library preparations of genetic material, rather than targeting single amplicons as in traditional Sanger sequencing. Also called Next Generation Sequencing (NGS)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[ingest]]Ingestion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:33
msgid "Process of importing data from heterogeneous sources, such as local databases, text files or spreadsheets, to a common destination system, such as an online <<biodiversity-data-platform, biodiversity data platform>>, for storage and further analysis. Typically includes steps of extraction, transformation (cleaning) and loading (ETL)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[index]]Indexing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:34
msgid "Organization of information in accordance with a specific schema or structure, making data easier to access and present."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[insdc]]International Nucleotide Sequence Database Collaboration (INSDC)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:35
msgid "Joint effort of the DNA Databank of Japan (DDBJ), <<embl,EMBL>> and <<ncbi,NCBI>> to provide global public access to nucleotide sequence data and associated information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[metagenomics]]Metagenomics"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:36
msgid "PCR-free sequencing of random genomic fragments in a mixed sample."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[mixs]]Minimum Information about any (x) Sequence (MIxS) standard"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:37
msgid "Family of standards (checklists) for sequence metadata, developed by the Genomic Standards Consortium (GSC)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[motu]]molecular Operational Taxonomic Unit (mOTU)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:38
msgid "See <<otu,Operational Taxonomic Unit (OTU)>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[ncbi]]National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:39
msgid "Division of United States National Library of Medicine (NLM) housing important bioinformatics resources, such as the GenBank database of DNA sequences, and the <<sra,Sequence Read Archive (SRA)>> of high throughput sequencing data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[ngs]]Next Generation Sequencing (NGS)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:40
msgid "See <<hts,High-throughput sequencing (HTS)>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[occurrence]]Occurrence"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:41
msgid "An existence of an Organism (sensu http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/Organism) at a particular place at a particular time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[otu]]Operational Taxonomic Unit (OTU)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:42
msgid "Cluster of organisms based on similarity in specific DNA marker sequence(s), used for taxonomic classification. Includes, for example, <<sh,Species Hypothesis>> in UNITE, and <<bins,Barcode Index Numbers>> in the Barcode of Life Data System (BOLD). <<asv,Amplicon Sequence Variants (ASVs)>> may be considered analogous to <<zotu,zero radius OTUs (zOTUs)>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[pcr]]Polymerase Chain Reaction (PCR)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:43
msgid "Technique for fast amplification and detection of specific fragments of target DNA (or RNA) sequences. Amplified regions are determined by the pair of <<primer,PCR primers>> used in the reaction."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[pipeline]]Pipeline"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:44
msgid "In bioinformatics, a set of algorithms or tools applied in a predefined workflow to process e.g. <<hts,High-throughput sequencing (HTS)>> data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[primer]]Primers (PCR primers)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:45
msgid "Short, synthetic, single-stranded DNA fragments that bind to a selected region of target DNA (marker) to initiate replication during <<pcr,PCR>>. A pair of primers is necessary for the polymerase enzyme to amplify the selected marker."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[qpcr]]qPCR (quantitative Polymerase Chain Reaction)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:46
msgid "Quantitative <<pcr,PCR>>. Method that measures relative DNA quantity of a marker in a sample. See also <<ddpcr,ddPCR>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:46
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[sample]]Sample"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:47
msgid "Material (water, soil, gut content, etc) obtained for analysis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[seq-align]]Sequence alignment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:48
msgid "Bioinformatic process of comparing and arranging two or more molecular (DNA, RNA or protein) sequences to detect similarities caused by e.g. evolutionary relatedness."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:48
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[sh]]Species Hypothesis (SH)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:49
msgid "Species-level <<otu,Operational Taxonomic Unit (OTU)>> as defined in the UNITE database and sequence management environment, for Fungi."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[specimen]]Specimen"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:50
msgid "An individual animal, plant, fungus, etc. used as an example of its species or type for scientific study or display."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[sra]]Sequence Read Archive (SRA)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:51
msgid "Public repository of high throughput (<<ngs,NGS>>) sequencing data, with instances operated by <<ncbi,the National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI)>>, <<embl,the European Bioinformatics Institute (EMBL-EBI)>>, and the DNA Data Bank of Japan (DDBJ). Includes both raw (non-denoised) sequencing output and <<seq-align,sequence alignments>>. One of three components of <<ena, the European Nucleotide Archive (ENA)>>, and previously known as the Short Read Archive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[tcs]]Target-capture sequencing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:52
msgid "Sequencing of DNA fragments isolated with hybridization probes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[unite]]UNITE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: glossary.en.adoc:53
msgid "UNITE is a web-based sequence management environment centred on the eukaryotic nuclear ribosomal ITS region. All public sequences are clustered into species hypotheses (SHs), which are assigned unique DOIs. An SH-matching service outputs various elements of information, including what species are present in eDNA samples, whether these species are potentially undescribed new species, other studies in which they were recovered, whether the species are alien to a region, and whether they are threatened. The DOIs are connected to the taxonomic backbone of the https://plutof.ut.ee/[PlutoF platform^] and https://www.gbif.org[GBIF^], such that they are accompanied by a taxon name where available. The data used in UNITE are hosted and managed in PlutoF. Data are represented through a range of standards, primarily https://dwc.tdwg.org/[Darwin Core^], https://gensc.org/mixs/[MIxS^], and https://github.com/RDA-DMP-Common/RDA-DMP-Common-Standard[DMP Common Standard^]; partial support is available for https://www.dcc.ac.uk/resources/metadata-standards/eml-ecological-metadata-language[EML^], https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20211251/[MCL^], and https://terms.tdwg.org/wiki/GGBN_Data_Standard[GGBN^]. PlutoF exports data primarily through the CSV and FASTA formats. PlutoF can also be used to publish data in GBIF (using the DwC format) and to prepare GenBank submission files. It is furthermore possible to download species lists from your data and download your project as a https://www.json.org/json-en.html[JSON] document with project data in hierarchically structured."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: glossary.en.adoc:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[zotu]]Zero radius otu (zOTU)"
msgstr ""

